race.comment: CUBAN WATERS (1) looks set to fire first-up on the back of a dominant trial win. Voorham sticks from the trial and from the low draw should take up a prominent spot before sprinting quickly. Can return with a bang. BELLENTIA (6) has the fitness edge and should be peaking third-up after a strong closing effort in town last time. Proven over this journey and is the clear main danger. REDWINELOVER (12) has only been fair in two runs back but went better than the form guide suggests last start behind a good winner. Backs up quickly and gets Crowther from a good draw. Can play a more significant role this time. WADAANA (5) has mixed her form but her run two back at Clare, when closing off into fourth, measures up. Competitive if she brings her best.
